The paper discusses topics related to game theory, mathematical logic, automata theory, and their applications to the specification, design, and verification of complex systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses game theory, which makes cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses automata theory, which makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the design and verification of complex systems, which makes cs.SE (Software Engineering) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses formal verification, which makes cs.PL (Programming Languages) a possible sub-category.
